oc:kn_2cfe57cf a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building any new automation workflow" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Identify the trigger (property change, scheduled, form submission) 2. Define enrollment/suppression criteria 3. Map actions in sequence (assignment → notification → task → escalation) 4. Set SLA timers for each escalation tier 5. Test with sample records 6. Monitor and tune thresholds" ;
    oc:stepOrder 1 .

oc:kn_33a18e61 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:PerformanceProfile ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When scheduling automated Salesforce Flows or HubSpot workflows" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Scheduled flows (daily digests, stale deal checks) should run during business hours to ensure timely human follow-up." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Alerts sent outside business hours get buried; optimal timing ensures reps see and act on them." ;
    oc:severityLevel "LOW" .

oc:kn_3f0528c6 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When configuring MQL alert and SLA escalation workflows" ;
    oc:directiveContent "MQL follow-up SLA must not exceed 4 hours for initial contact and 48 hours maximum before escalation/reassignment." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Response time directly correlates with conversion rates; unworked leads degrade pipeline quality." ;
    oc:severityLevel "CRITICAL" .

oc:kn_59f5a2d5 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When setting up daily lead activity digests or notification workflows" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Do not alert on every single lead activity — filter for meaningful activity (e.g., exclude single homepage visits from daily digests)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Alert fatigue causes reps to ignore all notifications, defeating the purpose of automation." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_7773705e a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When configuring closed-won handoff to customer success" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Deal closed → create customer record in CS tool 2. Add to onboarding project template 3. Send welcome email 4. Create dedicated Slack channel 5. Remove from all sales sequences 6. Assign CS owner by segment/territory" ;
    oc:stepOrder 3 .

oc:kn_79e001b6 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When configuring Calendly/SavvyCal integration with CRM" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Route meeting bookings to existing contact owners first, overriding round-robin, to maintain relationship continuity." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Prospects who already have a relationship with a specific rep should continue with that rep, not get randomly reassigned." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_a1bbc70f a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When configuring lead scoring thresholds that auto-promote to MQL" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Use suppression lists for existing customers and competitors in auto-MQL workflows based on lead scoring." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Existing customers already have an owner; competitors scoring high creates false pipeline." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_c7edb360 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:RecoveryTactic ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When a prospect fails to attend a scheduled meeting" ;
    oc:directiveContent "For no-show meetings, wait 30 minutes then send a reschedule email and create a follow-up task due the next business day." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Immediate reschedule attempts recover a significant percentage of no-shows; flagging after the second no-show prevents wasted rep time." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_d157e671 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When setting up round-robin meeting scheduling" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. Create team event with all eligible reps 2. Set distribution to equal distribution 3. Configure buffer times (15 min) and minimum notice (4 hours) 4. Wire webhook to CRM for contact matching 5. Override round-robin for existing contact owners 6. Set lifecycle stage to MQL for new bookings" ;
    oc:stepOrder 2 .

oc:kn_d65b5008 a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:Procedure ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building Zapier cross-tool lead intake automations" ;
    oc:directiveContent "1. New form submission → create/update CRM contact 2. Enrich with Clearbit 3. Post enriched data to Slack #new-leads 4. Create task in project management tool 5. If score threshold crossed → sync across marketing automation, retargeting, SDR outreach, and analytics" ;
    oc:stepOrder 4 .

oc:kn_dfb190d4 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When configuring pipeline hygiene automation" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Set stale deal thresholds per stage rather than globally (e.g., Discovery: 14 days, Proposal: 10 days, Negotiation: 21 days)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Different deal stages have different natural durations; a single threshold creates false positives and false negatives." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_e3bf979a a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When building lead assignment and routing workflows" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always exclude already-owned leads from round-robin reassignment in MQL workflows." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Reassigning a lead already being worked by a rep disrupts the relationship and creates confusion." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

